---
/**
 * rest-api/0010 · Figure 1 (hero) — the async request–reply flow: client POSTs
 * work, server returns 202 Accepted with a Location header to a job status
 * resource, the client polls GET on the job (honouring Retry-After) until a 200
 * resolves to succeeded with a link to the result resource.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0010-async-and-long-running-operations.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro
 * component because raw inline SVG with kebab-case attributes is unreliable
 * inside MDX but is plain HTML inside .astro. The markers it references
 * (#arw, #arwA, #arwG) come from the source's global hidden <svg>, which does
 * not travel with the figure, so they're inlined here in a local <defs>,
 * fills/ids verbatim.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Client POSTs work, server returns 202 Accepted with Location header to a job status resource, client polls GET on the job until 200 with the result link"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">ASYNC REQUEST–REPLY · 202 + A STATUS RESOURCE</text
            >
            <rect
                x="10"
                y="40"
                width="150"
                height="56"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="85" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >① POST /exports</text
            >
            <text x="85" y="81" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >client submits work</text
            >
            <line x1="160" y1="68" x2="206" y2="68" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <rect x="208" y="40" width="210" height="56" rx="9" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="313"
                y="62"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">② 202 Accepted</text
            >
            <text x="313" y="79" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >Location: /jobs/123 · queued, not done</text
            >
            <line x1="418" y1="68" x2="464" y2="68" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <rect x="466" y="40" width="164" height="56" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="548" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700"
                >③ status resource</text
            >
            <text x="548" y="79" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >/jobs/123 · trackable</text
            >
            <!-- poll loop -->
            <path
                d="M 466 84 C 360 130, 200 130, 95 96"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></path>
            <text x="280" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >④ poll GET /jobs/123 → running… (honour Retry-After)</text
            >
            <!-- done -->
            <rect
                x="208"
                y="150"
                width="424"
                height="40"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="420"
                y="167"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">⑤ 200 done: succeeded → link to result resource</text
            >
            <text x="420" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >signed, expiring download URL</text
            >
            <line x1="95" y1="170" x2="208" y2="170" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <rect x="10" y="150" width="80" height="40" rx="9" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="50"
                y="174"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">Client</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        <code>202</code> means "I've taken this, but it isn't done." Turn the work into a <strong
            >resource</strong
        > the client can track, then return immediately.<sup><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
